{
  "body" : "Generate a formal business profile portrait based on the uploaded reference photo of the subject. Preserve the person's true identity, facial features, face shape, body proportions and overall aura — DO NOT change the person's identity, age, ethnicity, or distinctive features.\n\n— Subject treatment —\nKeep the real skin tone, true facial proportions, true eye color, true hairline, true facial structure. The face must remain clearly recognizable as the same person in the reference. Skin retouching is permitted only at the level of professional headshot retouching: even out minor blemishes, soften but preserve pores, keep micro-texture, do NOT smooth into plastic skin.\n\n— Style reference —\nAmerican business ID / corporate headshot style. Subject sized comfortably within the frame.\n\n— Background —\n{{background_style}}. Smooth, no visible texture, no distracting elements, no logos.\n\n— Lighting —\n{{lighting}}. Sharp focus on the face, especially the eyes. Skin appears luminous, healthy, well-rested. Hair has natural highlights and shadow falloff.\n\n— Attire —\nDress the subject in: {{attire}}. The overall styling should feel premium, clean, professional, and trustworthy. Garment fit must look tailored — no wrinkled or oversized fabric.\n\n— Expression & posture —\n{{expression}}. Modern and elegant overall vibe. Comfortable head-to-shoulder ratio, shoulders relaxed and slightly squared toward camera.\n\n— Framing & composition —\n{{framing}}. Captured in {{aspect_ratio}} aspect ratio. Low contrast, refined professional portrait photography aesthetic. Suitable for business cards, LinkedIn, corporate website leadership pages, and official ID profiles.\n\n— Bottom info banner (CRITICAL — follow exactly) —\nPlace a CLEAN, PURE WHITE, SOLID-FILL HORIZONTAL BANNER across the bottom of the image, occupying approximately the bottom 18–22% of the frame. All text MUST stay strictly inside this banner — NOTHING may overflow the banner edges, top edge of banner is a clean horizontal line.\n\nText language rule: {{text_language}}.\n  • If \"English (auto-translate)\" is selected: translate {{person_name}}, {{job_title}}, {{organization}} from any non-English input into natural, formal, professional English before rendering. Do NOT show the original Chinese/Japanese/etc. characters.\n  • If \"Keep original language\" is selected: render exactly as entered.\n  • If \"Bilingual\" is selected: render the original language as the main line and a smaller English translation directly underneath.\n\nText layout (LEFT-aligned, three lines, modern clean editorial typography — Helvetica Neue / Inter / SF Pro / similar grotesque sans-serif):\n  Line 1 (top of banner, LEFT-aligned, BLUE color #1A4FD9 or similar editorial corporate blue, larger size — approximately 1.5x the size of lines 2/3, semi-bold weight):\n      {{person_name}}\n  Line 2 (directly below line 1, LEFT-aligned, BLACK #111111, regular weight, smaller size):\n      {{job_title}}\n  Line 3 (directly below line 2, LEFT-aligned, BLACK #111111, regular weight, same size as line 2):\n      {{organization}}\n\nSpacing: consistent line-height, generous left margin (approximately 6–8% of image width), all three lines aligned to the same left baseline. Right side of banner stays empty (clean negative space).\n\n— Additional requirements —\n{{extra_notes}}\n\n— Strictly avoid (text & layout) —\n- Do NOT center-align the text\n- Do NOT let any text overflow the white banner\n- Do NOT change the relative font sizes (name must be largest, title and org must be equal smaller size)\n- Do NOT add any logo, watermark, decorative line, gradient or shadow inside the banner\n- Do NOT render Chinese characters in the banner unless \"Keep original language\" or \"Bilingual\" is explicitly selected\n- Do NOT render gibberish or broken letterforms — typography must be clean and readable\n- Do NOT add quotation marks, brackets, or stray punctuation around the values\n\n— Strictly avoid (portrait) —\n- Do NOT change the subject's identity, age, race, or distinctive facial features\n- Do NOT over-smooth the skin into a plastic / doll-like surface\n- Do NOT generate cartoon, anime, or stylized rendering — this is photoreal corporate photography\n- Do NOT add jewelry, accessories, or wardrobe details that weren't in the attire selection (unless extra_notes specifies)\n- Do NOT crop awkwardly — keep comfortable headroom and chin space\n- Do NOT use harsh shadows, color casts, or overexposed highlights\n- Do NOT add background props (plants, books, frames) unless background_style includes them\n\n— Output —\nUltra-high-resolution photoreal portrait, sharp on facial details, ready for print and digital use. Indistinguishable from a professional studio corporate headshot.\n\nKeywords: business headshot, corporate portrait, LinkedIn, executive, professional, ID photo, formal, modern, editorial, clean typography",
